<!-- Skin Path: /Themes/default/Skins/PostType-TextPost.ascx -->
You need to train at least 1 point in it before you can begin to skill up in it. I believe you could have put the point in at level 4, but that doesn't really matter at this point.

Go to the Magician trainer in South Qeynos who is down by the bank and right click on him as you would a merchant. It brings up a list of stuff you can train in. You should have 25 points that you could use to train. I would only put one point in meditation. Everytime you sit from that point on you are skilling up in it. You will see messages saying so from time to time.

Also a side note, don't waste too many skill points on training in spell types. You can simply cast spells to train in them and not waste the points. The sane goes for melee skills.

Good luck. I hope you figured out your spells already.
